WEBVTT

00:01.247 --> 00:03.464
MAXINE: <i>Mr. Beaumont,
why would you hire me</i>

00:03.466 --> 00:04.882
if you knew who my mother was?

00:04.884 --> 00:06.484
The question isn't why I hired you.

00:06.486 --> 00:07.852
It's why you'd want to work for the man

00:07.854 --> 00:09.320
<i>who got her killed.</i>

00:10.123 --> 00:11.789
(GASPS)

00:11.791 --> 00:12.990
<i>Damien Delaine</i>

00:12.992 --> 00:14.559
<i>wanted to become a martyr that day,</i>

00:14.561 --> 00:17.195
<i>and he will never forgive me.</i>

00:17.197 --> 00:18.396
Never.

00:19.979 --> 00:21.813
NATHALIE: <i>Didn't you promise Evie</i>

00:21.815 --> 00:23.014
you wouldn't track her anymore?

00:23.016 --> 00:24.682
It's for her own safety.

00:24.684 --> 00:26.818
NATHALIE: <i>She's your daughter.
You have to trust her.</i>

00:26.820 --> 00:28.453
- I'm back.
- Hello, sweetie.

00:28.455 --> 00:30.254
You gate-crashing our shopping trip?

00:30.256 --> 00:32.824
- Your mom's caught me working again.
- Uh-huh.

00:32.826 --> 00:34.125
This isn't over, Maxine.

00:34.127 --> 00:35.259
It is over.

00:35.261 --> 00:36.463
Delaine lost.

00:36.465 --> 00:38.083
He's not gonna accept defeat.

00:38.085 --> 00:40.264
(PHONE RINGS)

00:40.266 --> 00:41.767
- Eric.
- Nathalie, what's wrong?

00:41.769 --> 00:44.335
I put Evie on the plane
back to Montreal myself.

00:44.337 --> 00:46.137
The driver's waiting at arrivals.

00:46.139 --> 00:47.305
She never showed.

00:47.307 --> 00:49.040
I know something's wrong, Eric.

00:50.944 --> 00:52.911
Delaine's taken my daughter.

00:59.303 --> 01:01.303
_

01:04.654 --> 01:06.654
_

01:06.993 --> 01:09.160
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

01:11.000 --> 01:17.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:25.044 --> 01:26.611
You're Eric Beaumont?

01:26.613 --> 01:28.980
- That's right.
- He disabled the elevator.

01:28.982 --> 01:30.515
Oh, great.

01:39.679 --> 01:42.246
He says he'll jump if we go out there.

01:42.271 --> 01:43.871
He'll jump if we don't.

01:43.896 --> 01:45.214
Okay.

01:56.342 --> 01:58.109
Mr. Faber?

02:00.980 --> 02:04.415
You don't want to do this, Mr. Faber.

02:04.417 --> 02:06.384
(HELICOPTER WHIRRING)

02:11.658 --> 02:14.458
- I said no cops.
- See, I'm not a cop.

02:14.460 --> 02:16.060
My name's Eric Beaumont.

02:16.062 --> 02:17.728
I'm a negotiator.

02:17.730 --> 02:20.097
I got nothing to negotiate.

02:20.099 --> 02:21.365
My life is over.

02:21.367 --> 02:23.067
That is not true. I just ran eight blocks

02:23.069 --> 02:24.335
from your work. I talked to your boss.

02:24.337 --> 02:26.296
He says he's gonna find you another job.

02:27.307 --> 02:30.074
- You're lying.
- I don't lie, Jacob.

02:31.176 --> 02:32.977
That voice in your head,

02:34.012 --> 02:36.514
the one telling you to give up?

02:36.516 --> 02:38.216
Don't listen.

02:38.218 --> 02:40.051
Sorry.

02:41.254 --> 02:43.387
I just can't.

02:46.693 --> 02:48.059
(BOY CRYING) Go, go.

02:52.332 --> 02:54.131
Come on.

02:56.069 --> 02:57.401
(GRUNTS) Let go.

02:57.403 --> 02:58.970
I'm not gonna do that.

03:06.579 --> 03:08.679
I'll take you with me.

03:08.681 --> 03:11.449
I can't leave your son without a father.

03:11.451 --> 03:13.885
And he needs you.

03:22.762 --> 03:26.030
(”INTRO” BY THE XX PLAYING)

03:42.615 --> 03:44.882
♪ ♪

03:58.131 --> 04:01.183
That was really brave, Mr. Beaumont.

04:02.135 --> 04:03.901
Nathalie Denard.

04:03.903 --> 04:06.504
My company insures this hotel.

04:08.341 --> 04:10.641
That a-a French accent?

04:10.643 --> 04:12.122
I'm from Paris.

04:12.124 --> 04:14.178
People really eat snails over there?

04:14.180 --> 04:16.279
And we talk like this, and...

04:16.281 --> 04:18.315
- Make great fries, though, right?
- Mmm.

04:18.317 --> 04:19.731
You're ex-FBI?

04:19.733 --> 04:21.519
Yeah, I just started my own firm.

04:21.521 --> 04:23.774
Um, Crisis Resolution.

04:23.774 --> 04:25.240
Must be good at reading people.

04:25.242 --> 04:27.342
Absolutely, the best.
I'm reading you right now,

04:27.344 --> 04:29.377
- as a matter of fact. Mm-hmm.
- Are you?

04:29.379 --> 04:30.941
You're wondering if I

04:30.966 --> 04:33.048
- find you attractive.
- Oh.

04:33.050 --> 04:35.183
- How are you getting that?
- Microexpressions,

04:35.185 --> 04:37.452
voice latency, the way the vein
in your neck is throbbing.

04:37.454 --> 04:39.521
But mostly because I'm thinking that,

04:39.523 --> 04:41.389
and I thought it would
be nice if that's what...

04:41.391 --> 04:42.991
you were also thinking.

04:42.993 --> 04:44.326
(CHUCKLES)

04:44.328 --> 04:46.661
(LAUGHS)

04:54.823 --> 04:56.823
_

04:59.643 --> 05:01.810
(SIGHS)

05:06.517 --> 05:08.750
I never should have left Evie

05:08.752 --> 05:10.886
to fly home without me.
You couldn't know.

05:10.888 --> 05:12.888
If I had just stayed with her,
she wouldn't be kidnapped.

05:12.890 --> 05:14.623
Hey, hey. Neither of us
knew this would happen.

05:14.625 --> 05:16.658
You can't blame yourself, okay?

05:16.660 --> 05:18.827
We got something.

05:25.502 --> 05:29.571
CCTV footage from the airport
seven hours ago.

05:29.573 --> 05:32.240
MAXINE: It's Damien Delaine
posing as her limo driver.

05:32.242 --> 05:33.341
(HITS TABLE)

05:33.343 --> 05:35.310
That's proof that he violated his parole.

05:35.312 --> 05:37.479
And Delaine never said
anything to you about this?

05:37.481 --> 05:39.414
You think I wouldn't have told you that?

05:41.985 --> 05:44.753
She didn't even know that
she was being kidnapped.

05:46.590 --> 05:48.190
Well, she knows now.

05:48.192 --> 05:49.558
What's he done with her?

05:49.560 --> 05:51.459
(PHONE RINGING)

06:00.637 --> 06:02.437
Crisis Resolution.

06:02.439 --> 06:03.848
DELAINE: Maxine.

06:03.850 --> 06:05.941
Lovely to hear your voice.

06:06.391 --> 06:08.777
We know you took Evie, Damien.

06:08.779 --> 06:11.146
Of course I did.

06:11.148 --> 06:14.816
I've just sent proof she's alive
to Mr. Yates.

06:18.088 --> 06:19.788
(NATHALIE GASPS)

06:19.790 --> 06:21.022
Evie.

06:21.024 --> 06:22.691
I will negotiate with Eric

06:22.693 --> 06:24.025
and only Eric.

06:24.027 --> 06:26.795
Breathe a word of this to the police,

06:26.797 --> 06:28.864
and the girl dies.

06:28.866 --> 06:30.398
(DIAL TONE)

06:30.400 --> 06:32.067
Oh, baby.

06:32.069 --> 06:33.768
At least he's willing to negotiate.

06:33.770 --> 06:35.136
Eric.

06:35.138 --> 06:37.205
He doesn't care about Evie.

06:37.207 --> 06:39.608
She's just a way to get what he wants.

06:39.610 --> 06:41.109
Which is what?

06:41.111 --> 06:44.212
Damien Delaine wants to destroy Eric.

06:44.214 --> 06:46.414
He won't stop until he has.

06:54.591 --> 06:56.858
♪ ♪

07:06.593 --> 07:14.613
Synced & corrected by -robtor-
www.addic7ed.com

07:18.727 --> 07:20.293
Delaine skirted CCTV

07:20.295 --> 07:21.227
at the airport.

07:21.229 --> 07:22.729
There's no way to track his vehicle

07:22.731 --> 07:24.464
- without the police.
- MAXINE: And he said no police.

07:24.466 --> 07:26.032
NATHALIE: Well, maybe we
should call them anyway.

07:26.034 --> 07:28.301
We do that, we'll never see Evie again.

07:28.804 --> 07:30.103
Delaine doesn't bluff.

07:30.105 --> 07:32.305
There must be something we can do.

07:32.307 --> 07:33.740
Zara stayed behind in Virginia

07:33.742 --> 07:35.642
to see if Delaine dropped
any bread crumbs.

07:35.644 --> 07:37.143
Mobile phones, credit cards...

07:37.145 --> 07:39.212
Well, the man is a master
of digital manipulation.

07:39.214 --> 07:40.647
He'll have covered his tracks.

07:41.194 --> 07:43.615
- She's checking anyway.
- Profile's up.

07:43.617 --> 07:45.369
We know Delaine's profile.

07:45.806 --> 07:48.521
This is our protocol, Eric, remember?

07:48.523 --> 07:49.989
We don't need to talk. We need to act.

07:49.991 --> 07:51.257
He has taken my daughter.

07:51.259 --> 07:53.893
All the more reason
to follow the protocol.

07:53.895 --> 07:55.995
(SIGHS)

08:00.102 --> 08:01.631
Go ahead.

08:05.107 --> 08:06.272
OLIVER: Delaine was an outspoken critic

08:06.274 --> 08:08.274
of digital technology.

08:08.276 --> 08:09.716
Back in 2000, he argued

08:09.718 --> 08:11.442
that the world would be
taken over by the Internet,

08:11.444 --> 08:14.247
robbing people
of their privacy and freedom.

08:14.249 --> 08:15.682
This is what the cult at Shiloh

08:15.684 --> 08:18.218
<i>was trying to stop
until the FBI moved in.</i>

08:21.003 --> 08:22.522
<i>37 people were killed,</i>

08:22.524 --> 08:23.957
including...

08:23.959 --> 08:25.391
Maxine's mother.

08:32.701 --> 08:34.400
Delaine was released last week

08:34.402 --> 08:37.236
<i>on parole after serving
17 years in prison.</i>

08:37.239 --> 08:39.339
Well, he wasted no time coming after you.

08:39.341 --> 08:40.940
Well, not directly.

08:40.942 --> 08:42.275
Not at first.

08:42.277 --> 08:43.943
MAXINE: He brainwashed a former student,

08:43.945 --> 08:45.278
<i>Victoria Locke,</i>

08:45.280 --> 08:47.413
<i>with the aim to destroy Eric</i>

08:47.415 --> 08:49.382
<i>by tricking him into killing her.</i>

08:49.384 --> 08:50.683
He thought Maxine would turn
against us when she learned

08:50.685 --> 08:52.852
that Eric killed her
mother, but she didn't.

08:55.018 --> 08:57.957
I know you were just doing
what you had to do.

08:57.959 --> 08:59.626
I don't blame you.

08:59.628 --> 09:02.395
- (EXHALES)
- So taking Evie was what?

09:02.397 --> 09:04.197
A backup plan
because his trick didn't work?

09:04.199 --> 09:05.165
Possibly.

09:05.167 --> 09:06.566
If it was improvised,

09:06.568 --> 09:07.500
maybe he made a mistake.

09:07.502 --> 09:09.469
Delaine doesn't make mistakes.

09:09.471 --> 09:12.672
Like Maxine said, he won't stop
until he destroys me.

09:12.674 --> 09:15.475
Which is why this is a toxic negotiation.

09:15.477 --> 09:16.674
Why toxic?

09:16.676 --> 09:19.245
Eric's perspective will be blurred

09:19.247 --> 09:21.347
because he's negotiating
for the life of a loved one.

09:21.349 --> 09:23.183
OLIVER: He should recuse himself,

09:23.185 --> 09:24.517
but since Delaine insists

09:24.519 --> 09:26.219
on negotiating with him,

09:26.221 --> 09:27.921
he's gonna need a whisperer.

09:27.923 --> 09:30.256
- A shadow.
- I'll monitor his every decision,

09:30.258 --> 09:31.302
make sure he doesn't act out

09:31.327 --> 09:33.050
- of emotion.
- No, no, Maxine.

09:34.429 --> 09:36.429
This is toxic for you, too,

09:36.431 --> 09:38.144
given his history with your mother.

09:38.973 --> 09:40.740
Oliver will be my whisperer.

09:41.314 --> 09:43.603
(PHONE RINGING)

09:49.744 --> 09:51.611
Hello, Cri/Res.

09:53.835 --> 09:55.535
Okay.

09:58.320 --> 10:00.291
It's Delaine. He's downstairs.

10:01.075 --> 10:03.142
He wants to come up.

10:13.735 --> 10:15.134
(ELEVATOR BELL CHIMES)

10:18.173 --> 10:19.602
Mr. Yates.

10:21.312 --> 10:23.176
Very nice place you have, Eric.

10:23.178 --> 10:25.745
Must have made a lot of money
off other people's misery

10:25.747 --> 10:28.848
while I was rotting in jail.

10:28.850 --> 10:31.284
You'll rot there again soon enough.

10:31.286 --> 10:32.907
You think?

10:34.756 --> 10:37.690
You're very lovely, Nathalie.

10:37.692 --> 10:40.693
I can see why Eric prizes you so much.

10:40.695 --> 10:43.062
I know you think I'm a
monster, but believe me,

10:43.064 --> 10:46.299
any evil I've done is nothing
compared to your husband.

10:46.301 --> 10:47.678
Evil?

10:47.680 --> 10:49.331
He prevented my martyrdom

10:49.333 --> 10:51.170
and brought about the world we live in.

10:51.172 --> 10:52.939
And what world is that?

10:53.775 --> 10:55.700
Endless cyber warfare,

10:55.702 --> 10:58.437
digital chaos, people addicted

10:58.439 --> 10:59.999
to their devices,

10:59.999 --> 11:01.632
entertaining themselves to death,

11:01.634 --> 11:04.802
while corporations and
government monitor and control

11:04.804 --> 11:07.571
the way we vote and think.

11:07.573 --> 11:09.873
I should make a martyr of you right now.

11:09.875 --> 11:12.209
And never see your daughter
again? I don't think so.

11:12.211 --> 11:13.544
You <i> are</i> a monster.

11:13.546 --> 11:15.212
You tried to get me to betray Eric

11:15.214 --> 11:17.214
by twisting the truth about my mother.

11:17.216 --> 11:20.417
You disappointed me in the end, Maxine.

11:21.372 --> 11:22.519
Just like she did.

11:22.521 --> 11:24.788
- Go to hell, Damien.
- What do you want?

11:25.624 --> 11:28.125
To talk, of course.

11:28.127 --> 11:30.173
That's what you people
are good at, isn't it?

11:31.263 --> 11:32.663
We're listening.

11:33.593 --> 11:35.099
I'm gonna ask some questions.

11:35.101 --> 11:37.334
If you fail to answer truthfully,

11:37.764 --> 11:39.269
the girl dies.

11:39.271 --> 11:40.704
(GASPS, GROANS)

11:40.706 --> 11:41.972
What kind of questions?

11:41.974 --> 11:43.707
Oh, don't worry, Mr. Yates.

11:43.709 --> 11:46.810
(WHISPERS): Eric won't need
a whisperer for this.

11:50.716 --> 11:53.050
(FAINT BEEPING)

11:59.058 --> 12:00.724
It's difficult getting the truth

12:00.726 --> 12:03.694
from a silver-tongued liar
like yourself, Eric.

12:03.696 --> 12:05.929
Hurt Evie, and I break your neck.

12:05.931 --> 12:08.298
- How's that for truth?
- (CLICKING TONGUE)

12:08.770 --> 12:10.467
Such violence.

12:11.214 --> 12:12.936
Are you ready, Mr. Yates?

12:12.938 --> 12:14.138
Ready.

12:14.943 --> 12:17.307
First, the obvious question.

12:17.309 --> 12:20.644
You admit to being in love
with Maxine's mother,

12:20.646 --> 12:22.646
Jessica Ford?

12:22.648 --> 12:23.981
I admit it.

12:23.983 --> 12:26.316
(BEEPING)

12:26.318 --> 12:28.385
And despite the official FBI account,

12:28.387 --> 12:30.387
you confess to killing her

12:30.389 --> 12:31.955
in cold blood?

12:32.568 --> 12:33.991
ERIC: To stop her from detonating

12:33.993 --> 12:35.959
an explosive vest, yes.

12:35.961 --> 12:37.861
I ask the questions, Eric.

12:37.863 --> 12:40.130
You answer yes or no.

12:40.132 --> 12:42.132
Yes, I killed her.

12:42.704 --> 12:44.334
Though I wish I would have killed you.

12:44.336 --> 12:45.636
Go ahead,

12:45.638 --> 12:47.771
check your graph.

12:48.841 --> 12:51.408
On to happier topics. There's a member

12:51.410 --> 12:54.678
of your team that I've often
wondered about... Zara Hallam.

12:55.591 --> 12:57.014
What about her?

12:57.016 --> 12:58.582
She's so loyal.

12:58.584 --> 13:01.218
Working endless hours,
traveling the world with you,

13:01.220 --> 13:03.320
while her husband
and children languish at home.

13:03.322 --> 13:05.355
Her relationship with you strikes me

13:05.357 --> 13:08.358
- as more than professional.
- You don't have to listen to this.

13:08.360 --> 13:09.660
He can't hurt me.

13:09.662 --> 13:10.827
Your pretty wife has no idea,

13:10.829 --> 13:13.797
but you two have slept together,
have you not?

13:13.799 --> 13:16.033
(NATHALIE SIGHS)

13:16.529 --> 13:17.834
No.

13:17.836 --> 13:19.036
(BEEPING)

13:21.607 --> 13:24.241
(TAKES DEEP BREATH)

13:26.080 --> 13:27.744
Go figure.

13:28.458 --> 13:30.414
Oliver Yates.

13:30.416 --> 13:32.616
He told you he wants you to give him

13:32.618 --> 13:34.518
his own team.

13:34.520 --> 13:35.852
Did you tell him that?

13:35.854 --> 13:37.554
Yeah.

13:37.556 --> 13:39.223
Yes, he did.

13:39.225 --> 13:41.058
You said you'd consider it.

13:41.060 --> 13:43.493
But you have no intention
of doing so, do you?

13:44.597 --> 13:46.530
No, I don't.

13:46.532 --> 13:48.232
- (BEEPING)
- (CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

13:50.146 --> 13:51.735
I'm fine.

13:54.840 --> 13:57.274
One more question, Eric.

13:57.276 --> 13:59.810
And remember, no lying.

14:01.146 --> 14:03.547
The risks you take saving lives,

14:03.549 --> 14:07.784
most people see it as heroism,
but we know it's not.

14:07.786 --> 14:09.201
Do we?

14:09.226 --> 14:11.188
You're racked with guilt
over Jessica's death.

14:11.190 --> 14:12.835
You're blazing with self-loathing.

14:12.837 --> 14:14.308
You dare not kill yourself,

14:14.310 --> 14:15.926
but if someone was to take your life

14:15.928 --> 14:18.662
in the line of duty,
that would be... (INHALES)

14:18.664 --> 14:20.397
a relief.

14:20.885 --> 14:23.600
That's why you're always
so happy to play the hero.

14:23.602 --> 14:25.102
Always the hero.

14:25.104 --> 14:26.937
Isn't that right, Eric?

14:33.606 --> 14:35.379
I don't know.

14:36.415 --> 14:38.382
(BEEPING)

14:40.552 --> 14:42.019
You don't know?

14:43.689 --> 14:45.952
Well, maybe now you do.

14:50.498 --> 14:53.307
Follow me or have me tracked,
and you'll never find her.

14:53.309 --> 14:56.027
- He's answered your questions.
- Tell us where she is.

14:56.029 --> 14:57.434
I've got three wishes.

14:57.436 --> 14:59.836
Answering the questions was my first.

14:59.838 --> 15:01.467
MAXINE: What are the others?

15:03.094 --> 15:05.542
I have a plane to catch at 1:30 tomorrow.

15:05.544 --> 15:07.344
I'm seeing my parole officer in New York.

15:07.346 --> 15:08.378
Grant my wishes

15:08.380 --> 15:10.280
by then, she lives.

15:10.282 --> 15:11.481
What are they?

15:11.483 --> 15:13.383
All in good time.

15:15.220 --> 15:17.888
You really are very lovely, Nathalie.

15:27.433 --> 15:30.067
♪ ♪

15:51.855 --> 15:53.619
(SIGHS)

15:57.913 --> 15:59.846
She's scared and alone.

16:00.583 --> 16:01.748
Knowing that psychopath

16:01.750 --> 16:04.150
- could kill her at any moment.
- You'll stop him.

16:04.152 --> 16:05.719
You're smarter than he is.

16:05.721 --> 16:07.320
Am I?

16:07.322 --> 16:09.689
Delaine's a genius.

16:11.993 --> 16:15.895
He preys on people's
weaknesses to hurt them.

16:16.250 --> 16:18.932
Whatever your demons are,

16:18.934 --> 16:20.900
you're a good man, Eric.

16:21.380 --> 16:23.103
You still believe in me.

16:23.799 --> 16:25.472
I always will.

16:27.442 --> 16:28.932
What?

16:28.957 --> 16:31.435
You said Delaine preys
on people's weaknesses.

16:33.476 --> 16:35.882
How did he know ours?

16:38.387 --> 16:39.953
Sit rep?

16:39.955 --> 16:42.389
Intonation and latency
are flat, colorless.

16:42.391 --> 16:43.990
Delaine gave us nothing.

16:43.992 --> 16:45.358
Except the questions he asked.

16:45.360 --> 16:47.160
His questions were
insightful and required

16:47.162 --> 16:49.763
intimate knowledge of my
relationships with each of you.

16:49.765 --> 16:51.364
How did he get that knowledge?

16:51.366 --> 16:53.366
By compromising our computer systems,

16:53.368 --> 16:56.369
accessing our confidential
e-mails and personal records.

16:56.371 --> 16:59.105
That would be consistent with
his expertise with computers.

16:59.107 --> 17:00.874
But he wouldn't have had access

17:00.876 --> 17:03.728
- to computers in prison.
- His pal Victoria Locke would have.

17:03.730 --> 17:05.381
OLIVER: I can check. If there's a breach

17:05.383 --> 17:06.980
in the files,
I should be able to locate it.

17:06.982 --> 17:09.482
- And how would that help us?
- Well, Delaine is a game player.

17:09.483 --> 17:11.217
Right now he's holding
all the cards... we need

17:11.219 --> 17:12.752
someone who can help us improve our odds.

17:12.753 --> 17:13.887
Someone like Victoria Locke.

17:13.888 --> 17:15.021
OLIVER: Well, Delaine brainwashed

17:15.022 --> 17:16.455
Victoria Locke for over a decade.

17:16.458 --> 17:18.023
She's not being brainwashed now.

17:18.026 --> 17:19.726
Yeah, but she was institutionalized

17:19.728 --> 17:20.993
in Virginia yesterday.

17:20.996 --> 17:23.029
Deprogramming her could take weeks,

17:23.031 --> 17:24.297
months even.

17:24.299 --> 17:25.898
We only have...

17:25.901 --> 17:28.101
12 hours until Delaine's deadline.

17:28.103 --> 17:30.590
I'll call Zara.
She can try talking to her.

17:31.383 --> 17:32.405
Nathalie?

17:32.407 --> 17:34.507
Delaine wants to destroy you,

17:34.509 --> 17:36.676
and he won't stop until he has.

17:36.678 --> 17:38.645
So why not just kill Evie, then?

17:38.647 --> 17:40.780
What's worse than that?

17:42.918 --> 17:45.185
♪ ♪

18:00.869 --> 18:03.369
(LIQUID DRIPPING)

18:03.371 --> 18:06.072
DELAINE: <i>Please don't fear me, Evie.</i>

18:06.946 --> 18:08.741
I just want to help you.

18:08.743 --> 18:12.178
I've got nothing to say to you.

18:13.482 --> 18:16.416
Your father prepared you
for an event like this.

18:16.418 --> 18:18.751
He would have told you to stay calm,

18:19.707 --> 18:22.822
not to engage with your kidnapper.

18:25.894 --> 18:28.461
Oh, Evie, you just...

18:28.463 --> 18:30.563
want to go home, don't you?

18:30.565 --> 18:32.832
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

18:32.834 --> 18:34.501
Evie,

18:34.503 --> 18:35.806
where is home?

18:37.006 --> 18:40.061
You're in boarding school
ten months out of the year,

18:41.145 --> 18:44.677
while your parents gallivant
across the world.

18:44.679 --> 18:46.813
My parents are working.

18:46.815 --> 18:47.881
Yes.

18:47.883 --> 18:49.682
Yes, they are.

18:49.684 --> 18:51.684
But...

18:51.686 --> 18:54.020
you're their only child, Evie.

18:55.284 --> 18:57.244
Shouldn't you come first?

19:00.262 --> 19:02.662
I never had any children.

19:02.664 --> 19:06.432
Your father put me in prison,
so I never led a normal life.

19:06.434 --> 19:08.201
You should still be there.

19:08.881 --> 19:10.737
Perhaps.

19:12.707 --> 19:14.941
But I paid for my crimes.

19:15.304 --> 19:17.210
And your father didn't.

19:20.015 --> 19:21.477
Evie...

19:23.521 --> 19:24.851
I took the SIM card out.

19:24.853 --> 19:26.719
But...

19:26.721 --> 19:29.389
there's still music and games.

19:37.699 --> 19:39.966
♪ ♪

19:41.903 --> 19:43.603
(CRYING)

19:45.472 --> 19:47.073
(DOOR HINGES SQUEAKING)

19:47.075 --> 19:49.442
(CLOSING DOOR ECHOES)

19:55.560 --> 19:59.453
_

19:59.588 --> 20:01.788
(LOW, INDISTINCT CHATTER)

20:01.790 --> 20:03.957
(PHONE RINGING)

20:05.660 --> 20:06.893
Hey, Max.

20:06.895 --> 20:08.628
Hey. You're at St. Agatha's?

20:08.630 --> 20:09.796
Yeah. I just got here.

20:09.798 --> 20:11.364
I'm on my way to see Victoria now.

20:11.366 --> 20:12.932
Everything okay?

20:12.934 --> 20:14.667
Listen, Zara, I...

20:14.669 --> 20:16.336
I need to apologize.

20:16.338 --> 20:17.804
For what?

20:17.806 --> 20:20.106
I lied when I said
I hadn't been in contact

20:20.108 --> 20:22.241
- with Damien Delaine.
- You thought Delaine could answer

20:22.243 --> 20:23.910
questions about your mother.

20:23.912 --> 20:25.745
I just... want you to know

20:25.747 --> 20:29.115
that as soon as we find Evie,
I'm resigning.

20:29.117 --> 20:32.352
Delaine thought he
could use you to destroy Eric,

20:32.354 --> 20:35.822
and instead, you saved him...
you saved all of us.

20:35.824 --> 20:38.825
- Ma'am?
- Look, you are like a sister to me.

20:38.827 --> 20:41.661
Delaine is still out there, and
we need to stick together, Max.

20:41.663 --> 20:43.529
Now more than ever.

20:43.531 --> 20:45.298
Okay?

20:45.300 --> 20:47.855
I'll call you as soon as I'm done.

20:52.974 --> 20:54.974
(BEEPING)

20:55.977 --> 20:58.077
She prefers to stay in the dark.

20:58.079 --> 21:00.701
She thinks that way Delaine
won't be able to find her.

21:01.416 --> 21:03.049
Victoria?

21:03.051 --> 21:04.951
Can you see me?

21:05.456 --> 21:07.082
VICTORIA: Yes.

21:07.656 --> 21:10.390
ZARA: Thank you for speaking with me.

21:10.392 --> 21:12.191
VICTORIA: Does he know you're here?

21:12.193 --> 21:15.261
Damien Delaine? No.

21:15.263 --> 21:18.798
VICTORIA: He sees everything, you know.

21:18.800 --> 21:22.802
You might think you're safe,
but you're not, anywhere, ever.

21:22.804 --> 21:25.171
ZARA: You are safe, Victoria.

21:25.173 --> 21:26.673
No one's gonna hurt you here.

21:26.675 --> 21:29.008
VICTORIA: He got inside my head.

21:29.010 --> 21:31.106
But he is out of your head now.

21:31.713 --> 21:33.880
And I need your help.

21:36.885 --> 21:38.364
For what?

21:38.790 --> 21:41.354
Delaine has kidnapped
Eric Beaumont's daughter.

21:41.356 --> 21:44.190
Oh, no. No, no.

21:44.192 --> 21:46.659
- No, no, no, no, no.
- Victoria.

21:46.661 --> 21:49.529
No. It's my fault, you see?

21:49.531 --> 21:51.464
He had me hack into your files.

21:51.466 --> 21:53.232
If she's in danger, it's because of me.

21:53.234 --> 21:56.199
If you can tell us anything,
anything at all.

21:56.201 --> 21:58.871
Don't you see? He's going to kill me.

21:59.468 --> 22:00.773
He's going to kill everyone.

22:00.775 --> 22:03.042
We are not gonna let that happen.

22:03.044 --> 22:05.227
VICTORIA: You can't stop him, no one can.

22:05.229 --> 22:07.513
I'm sorry. I-I don't know anything.

22:07.515 --> 22:09.716
Please, please go.

22:09.718 --> 22:11.855
Victoria, I have come all this way.

22:13.649 --> 22:15.455
Your colleague, Maxine,

22:15.457 --> 22:17.457
she was Jessica's daughter.

22:17.459 --> 22:18.691
That's right.

22:18.693 --> 22:21.527
Jessica had fire in her eyes.

22:21.529 --> 22:23.596
And then Damien got inside her head,

22:23.598 --> 22:25.298
just like he got inside mine.

22:25.300 --> 22:28.334
He took her to hell and back.

22:29.290 --> 22:31.471
You understand?

22:33.875 --> 22:36.642
I hope you find Evie.

22:42.218 --> 22:43.751
MAXINE: I just spoke to Zara.

22:43.753 --> 22:45.119
She confirmed Victoria Locke

22:45.121 --> 22:46.754
breached our firewall two months ago.

22:46.756 --> 22:48.456
Without our even knowing it.

22:48.458 --> 22:50.098
Pretty damn slick.

22:50.100 --> 22:52.793
Delaine said digital technology
would become a weapon.

22:52.795 --> 22:54.529
Now he's the one using it.

22:54.531 --> 22:57.131
(PHONE RINGING)

23:05.475 --> 23:06.974
This is Eric.

23:06.976 --> 23:08.976
DELAINE: Not even a “hello”?

23:08.978 --> 23:11.185
Where are your manners?

23:11.187 --> 23:14.315
Hello, Maxine, Mr. Yates, Ms. Denard.

23:14.317 --> 23:15.616
Where is our daughter?

23:15.618 --> 23:16.933
DELAINE: First things first.

23:16.935 --> 23:18.886
You wanted to know my second wish.

23:18.888 --> 23:21.789
Eric will meet me at
2000 St. Alexander Street

23:21.791 --> 23:23.024
in 30 minutes.

23:23.026 --> 23:24.458
He'll come alone.

23:26.796 --> 23:28.329
It's an office building.

23:28.331 --> 23:32.500
Tenants include property
developers, investment brokers.

23:32.502 --> 23:34.438
There's nothing out of the ordinary.

23:35.471 --> 23:39.548
Except... Viktor Volynets.

23:39.550 --> 23:40.941
A Russian oligarch,

23:40.943 --> 23:43.077
immigrated from Moscow in 2014.

23:43.079 --> 23:46.581
Assassinated dozens of his enemies.

23:48.384 --> 23:51.552
NATHALIE: (SIGHS) What does a Russian
oligarch have to do with Damien Delaine?

23:51.554 --> 23:52.753
You're not gonna play his game?

23:52.755 --> 23:54.755
Send those files to my phone, will you?

23:57.160 --> 23:59.360
(NATHALIE EXHALES)

23:59.362 --> 24:02.930
♪ Shadows settle on the place ♪

24:02.932 --> 24:04.232
♪ That you left ♪

24:04.234 --> 24:05.499
(DOOR OPENS)

24:05.501 --> 24:08.302
♪ Our minds are troubled by... ♪

24:08.304 --> 24:11.606
(DOOR CLOSES)

24:16.246 --> 24:18.346
I thought you might be hungry.

24:21.818 --> 24:24.051
It's my favorite.

24:24.053 --> 24:25.553
Who told you that?

24:25.555 --> 24:28.033
The wonders of social media.

24:29.326 --> 24:31.359
I am so sorry
I couldn't take you somewhere

24:31.361 --> 24:34.862
more comfortable. (SIGHS)

24:34.864 --> 24:39.133
Still Daddy's good little girl.

24:41.404 --> 24:42.870
(SCOFFS, SIGHS)

24:42.872 --> 24:45.139
(GRUNTS)

24:46.943 --> 24:48.509
Do you know who your father is?

24:48.511 --> 24:51.212
I know he's a good man and you're not.

24:51.214 --> 24:52.446
I'm sorry, Evie,

24:52.448 --> 24:54.315
but your father is a narcissist

24:54.317 --> 24:56.217
and a manipulator, who will say

24:56.219 --> 24:58.786
and do anything to get what he wants.

24:59.873 --> 25:01.088
The truth

25:01.090 --> 25:04.525
is hard to hear; believe me, I know.

25:05.445 --> 25:08.829
But the truth will set you free.

25:11.801 --> 25:13.855
When am I getting out of here?!

25:13.857 --> 25:17.305
Soon, Evie. Very soon.

25:25.782 --> 25:27.648
Is that better?

25:28.468 --> 25:30.518
(CRIES SOFTLY)

25:44.843 --> 25:46.843
_

26:06.956 --> 26:09.223
♪ ♪

26:18.715 --> 26:21.335
I see you're wearing your button cam.

26:21.337 --> 26:23.739
Hello, everyone.

26:24.900 --> 26:26.073
When I was in prison,

26:26.075 --> 26:30.511
they paid me $1.75
to make metal cabinets.

26:30.513 --> 26:33.881
Now that I'm a free man,
I find myself in need

26:33.883 --> 26:36.384
- of more substantial remuneration.
- How much?

26:36.386 --> 26:39.520
I don't want to be greedy,
but $100 million should do it.

26:39.522 --> 26:41.822
Well, obviously, I don't
have anywhere near that.

26:41.824 --> 26:44.797
I know, Eric. I've seen
your finances, remember?

26:44.799 --> 26:46.727
But you can get it.

26:47.770 --> 26:49.029
From the oligarch.

26:49.031 --> 26:51.832
Yeah. It seems crime does pay.

26:51.834 --> 26:54.201
The murderous Mr. Volynets

26:54.203 --> 26:57.371
has assets in excess of $2 billion.

26:57.373 --> 27:00.141
This is a self-executing program.

27:00.143 --> 27:01.976
Once inserted into the computer

27:01.978 --> 27:03.844
in his private office,
it will transfer $100 million

27:03.846 --> 27:07.014
from his criminal activities
into my offshore accounts.

27:10.319 --> 27:12.653
How do you expect me to get
into his private office?

27:12.655 --> 27:14.054
Well, talking your way in
shouldn't be a problem

27:14.056 --> 27:15.456
for a liar like you, Eric.

27:15.458 --> 27:17.324
(EXHALES)

27:17.326 --> 27:19.493
Look at it this way: if you die trying,

27:19.495 --> 27:21.498
all your problems will be over.

27:22.698 --> 27:24.293
But you better hurry.

27:25.168 --> 27:27.754
I have a flight to catch in two hours.

27:44.287 --> 27:46.320
(ERIC PANTING)

27:46.322 --> 27:47.955
Eric, you can't do this.

27:47.957 --> 27:49.223
Of course I can.

27:49.225 --> 27:50.524
OLIVER: No.
You'll be committing a felony.

27:50.526 --> 27:51.926
(LAUGHING): Are you kidding me?

27:51.928 --> 27:53.727
I won't live to face charges.

27:53.729 --> 27:55.830
And $100 million to
a criminal psychopath.

27:55.832 --> 27:57.498
What do you think Delaine's
gonna do with the money?

27:57.500 --> 27:59.066
Well, I guess I'll just
have to wait and see.

27:59.068 --> 28:01.302
Eric, you chose Oliver

28:01.304 --> 28:02.703
as your whisperer for a reason.

28:02.705 --> 28:04.305
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

28:04.307 --> 28:06.941
I don't do this and Delaine kills Evie.

28:08.778 --> 28:10.578
He's walking into a trap.

28:10.580 --> 28:12.046
- We have to find Evie.
- Yeah, we're trying.

28:12.048 --> 28:14.448
In 120 minutes, Delaine boards
a plane back to New York.

28:14.450 --> 28:17.685
<i>That's 120 minutes to save Evie and Eric.</i>

28:20.823 --> 28:23.357
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

28:31.067 --> 28:32.819
ERIC: Hi, Elena.

28:33.349 --> 28:34.548
Mr. Volynets, please.

28:34.904 --> 28:36.303
Do you have an appointment?

28:36.305 --> 28:37.805
My name is Damien Delaine.

28:37.807 --> 28:39.340
I was released
from federal prison last week,

28:39.342 --> 28:41.542
and I have urgent information
for Mr. Volynets

28:41.544 --> 28:43.410
regarding an FBI investigation.

28:43.412 --> 28:45.346
What did you say your name was? Delaine.

28:45.348 --> 28:47.481
D-E-L-A-I-N-E.

28:50.754 --> 28:52.786
Mr. Volynets.

28:52.788 --> 28:55.723
There's a gentleman here
that would like to see you.

28:57.427 --> 28:58.659
Damien Delaine.

28:59.221 --> 29:01.534
OLIVER: <i>You got any ideas, I'm all ears.</i>

29:04.367 --> 29:05.866
This is a negotiation, right?

29:05.868 --> 29:08.035
One where Delaine calculated
every decision point

29:08.037 --> 29:09.770
to make sure Eric does what he wants.

29:09.772 --> 29:11.472
Delaine always thinks ten steps ahead.

29:11.474 --> 29:13.641
And every step is the right one.

29:13.643 --> 29:15.009
What if it's not?

29:16.178 --> 29:18.045
Right this way, Mr. Delaine.

29:18.047 --> 29:19.647
Thank you so much, Elena.

29:20.200 --> 29:21.582
MAXINE: <i>Delaine knew we'd send Zara</i>

29:21.584 --> 29:23.450
<i>to talk to Victoria Locke.</i>

29:23.452 --> 29:25.419
NATHALIE: <i>But she didn't
say anything to Zara.</i>

29:25.421 --> 29:26.954
- Maybe she did.
- Zara just got on a flight

29:26.956 --> 29:28.289
out of Dulles an hour ago.

29:28.291 --> 29:30.291
Can you play the recording she sent you?

29:30.293 --> 29:32.393
- (SIGHS)
- (TYPES)

29:37.300 --> 29:39.867
Thank you so much, Elena.

29:42.772 --> 29:44.338
Mr. Delaine.

29:44.340 --> 29:45.839
What's this about?

29:45.841 --> 29:47.541
I just got out of Ossining, New York,

29:47.543 --> 29:49.743
where I befriended
a former associate of yours,

29:49.745 --> 29:51.545
Chokan Dushimov.

29:52.882 --> 29:54.776
And what about him?

29:55.217 --> 29:57.885
Chokan Dushimov has become
a federal informant.

29:57.887 --> 29:59.887
- You're lying.
- The American government

29:59.889 --> 30:01.488
is building a case against you based

30:01.490 --> 30:04.119
on his testimony, Mr. Volynets.

30:05.094 --> 30:07.261
There's no evidence against me.

30:07.263 --> 30:08.596
Oh, on the contrary.

30:08.598 --> 30:13.000
Mr. Dushimov has names, numbers,

30:13.002 --> 30:14.902
balances for all
of your offshore accounts,

30:14.904 --> 30:18.731
but he is willing to destroy them,

30:18.733 --> 30:20.774
if you make it worth his while.

30:21.303 --> 30:23.410
You think you can shake me down?

30:23.412 --> 30:24.778
(ERIC LAUGHS)

30:25.390 --> 30:27.648
A man's got to eat.

30:35.057 --> 30:37.319
You'll need to get it decrypted.

30:39.261 --> 30:41.095
Wait here.

30:42.431 --> 30:43.909
Sure.

30:44.634 --> 30:47.067
(DOOR OPENS, CLOSES)

31:03.853 --> 31:06.420
VICTORIA (ON RECORDING):
<i>He sees everything, you know.</i>

31:06.422 --> 31:10.367
You might think you're safe,
but you're not, anywhere, ever.

31:10.369 --> 31:11.965
ZARA: You are safe, Victoria.

31:11.967 --> 31:13.494
No one's gonna hurt you here.

31:13.496 --> 31:14.928
VICTORIA: Don't you see?

31:14.930 --> 31:16.597
- He's going to kill me.
- (PHONE RINGS)

31:16.599 --> 31:18.065
He's going to kill everyone.

31:18.067 --> 31:19.967
ZARA: We are not gonna let that happen.

31:19.969 --> 31:21.012
Oh, excuse me.

31:21.037 --> 31:22.062
VICTORIA: You can't stop it. No one can.

31:22.064 --> 31:23.103
- I'm sorry.
- Hello.

31:23.105 --> 31:24.371
VICTORIA: I don't know anything.

31:24.373 --> 31:26.607
DELAINE: Don't act surprised.

31:26.609 --> 31:29.043
Just walk away from the others.

31:31.847 --> 31:34.048
Okay.

31:37.753 --> 31:39.253
What do you want?

31:39.255 --> 31:41.055
DELAINE: My third wish.

31:41.057 --> 31:44.758
You got to do exactly as I say,
lovely Nathalie, to the word,

31:44.760 --> 31:48.529
or you'll never see your husband
or daughter again.

31:57.573 --> 31:59.139
Delaine!

31:59.141 --> 32:00.841
(DOOR CONTINUES RATTLING)

32:00.843 --> 32:03.343
Open this door now!

32:06.320 --> 32:07.987
(KNOCKING, RATTLING)

32:09.663 --> 32:11.773
VOLYNETS: Open this door now!

32:13.200 --> 32:14.699
VICTORIA: He took her to hell

32:14.701 --> 32:17.268
- and back. You understand?
- (BEEPS)

32:17.270 --> 32:19.270
- Play it again.
- Which part?

32:19.272 --> 32:20.704
- The whole thing.
- There's nothing there, Maxine.

32:20.706 --> 32:23.508
We've missed something. I know it.

32:25.254 --> 32:27.011
I'm going out for a smoke.

32:27.013 --> 32:28.613
Thought you quit.

32:28.615 --> 32:31.141
I did. I'll be back.

32:31.476 --> 32:33.251
VICTORIA: He got inside my head.

32:33.253 --> 32:34.719
I don't know how.

32:34.721 --> 32:36.688
(SHOUTS IN RUSSIAN)

32:37.591 --> 32:38.790
(SPEAKS RUSSIAN)

32:38.792 --> 32:40.942
(GRUNTING)

32:42.662 --> 32:44.963
(POUNDING ON DOOR)

32:48.034 --> 32:50.201
You, check the room.

32:56.076 --> 32:58.676
(GRUNTING)

33:00.280 --> 33:01.579
(MUTTERS IN RUSSIAN)

33:01.581 --> 33:02.881
(GRUNTING)

33:19.466 --> 33:21.566
(PANTS)

33:21.568 --> 33:23.434
VICTORIA: He took her to hell and back.

33:23.436 --> 33:26.538
You understand? I hope you find Evie.

33:26.540 --> 33:28.807
That's five times, Max.

33:32.045 --> 33:33.912
(PHONE CHIMES)

33:35.087 --> 33:37.087
_

33:39.419 --> 33:41.653
MAXINE: <i>“To hell and back.”</i>

33:42.420 --> 33:45.131
Maybe she wasn't talking about
my mother when she said that.

33:46.026 --> 33:49.327
She wanted to make sure
that we understood.

33:49.329 --> 33:51.462
She was telling us where Delaine

33:51.464 --> 33:52.864
took Evie.

33:52.866 --> 33:54.132
(BEEPS)

33:54.134 --> 33:55.934
She didn't mean “hell and back”"

33:55.936 --> 33:57.449
She meant “Hallenback”"

33:57.451 --> 33:59.103
It's an abandoned power plant.

33:59.105 --> 34:01.372
I'll call you from the car.

34:09.081 --> 34:11.516
(VEHICLE APPROACHES)

34:11.518 --> 34:13.117
(ENGINE TURNS OFF)

34:17.389 --> 34:19.657
- (EXHALES) I'm here.
- OLIVER: The place is abandoned.

34:19.659 --> 34:21.525
You shouldn't have too much
trouble getting into it.

34:21.527 --> 34:24.295
Just try to find an entrance somewhere.

34:41.281 --> 34:43.648
(SHUDDERING BREATHS)

34:52.391 --> 34:54.559
Nathalie?

34:54.561 --> 34:56.244
Eric...

34:56.795 --> 34:58.963
What are you doing here?

35:00.767 --> 35:03.626
Delaine's third wish.

35:05.272 --> 35:06.638
(WHIMPERS)

35:06.640 --> 35:09.440
(CRYING)

35:12.746 --> 35:15.246
Oliver, she could be anywhere.

35:15.248 --> 35:17.081
Pick a direction.

35:17.083 --> 35:19.284
Okay, okay.

35:19.286 --> 35:21.920
(PANTING)

35:21.922 --> 35:23.438
Evie?

35:24.591 --> 35:26.624
(CRYING)

35:26.626 --> 35:28.626
Nathalie, it's gonna be okay.

35:28.628 --> 35:30.895
It's gonna be okay.

35:30.897 --> 35:33.431
(NATHALIE CRYING)

35:33.433 --> 35:35.667
Eric, what the hell is that?

35:35.669 --> 35:37.243
Eric, talk to me.

35:37.671 --> 35:39.370
Evie?

35:42.108 --> 35:43.975
Evie?!

35:43.977 --> 35:45.710
(PHONE RINGS)

35:45.712 --> 35:47.312
(GASPS)

35:47.314 --> 35:49.681
(PHONE BEEPS)

35:51.705 --> 35:53.605
DELAINE: Give me to Eric.

35:53.630 --> 35:55.178
He wants to talk to you.

35:56.723 --> 35:58.957
(SHUDDERING)

35:58.959 --> 36:00.792
Where are you?

36:01.309 --> 36:03.094
I ask the questions and you answer.

36:03.096 --> 36:04.604
Remember?

36:05.665 --> 36:07.432
That's more like it.

36:07.434 --> 36:09.267
(PANTING)

36:09.269 --> 36:10.485
Evie?

36:11.204 --> 36:14.439
(PANTING)

36:14.441 --> 36:16.074
ERIC: I got your money.

36:16.076 --> 36:17.275
You did, indeed.

36:17.277 --> 36:19.277
And I'm prepared to release
your daughter,

36:19.279 --> 36:20.278
as promised.

36:20.280 --> 36:22.213
- Then you do it.
- Uh-uh.

36:22.215 --> 36:23.881
Not so fast.

36:23.883 --> 36:25.550
First, to say farewell,

36:25.552 --> 36:28.219
I'll leave you
with what I believe you call

36:28.221 --> 36:30.555
an oriented dilemma.

36:30.557 --> 36:31.990
(PANTING)

36:31.992 --> 36:33.925
An impossible choice.

36:33.927 --> 36:35.526
In plain English, yes.

36:35.528 --> 36:37.195
Evie?

36:37.197 --> 36:39.135
DELAINE: <i>If I let you disarm Nathalie...</i>

36:39.137 --> 36:40.798
MAXINE: <i>Evie?</i>

36:40.800 --> 36:42.667
DELAINE: <i>...Evie dies.</i>

36:42.669 --> 36:43.974
MAXINE: <i>Evie?!</i>

36:43.976 --> 36:46.637
If I release Evie,
then the lovely Nathalie

36:46.639 --> 36:48.131
goes up in smoke,

36:48.133 --> 36:50.174
just like poor Jessica.

36:50.176 --> 36:52.710
You can save one or the other, Eric.

36:52.712 --> 36:54.245
But not both.

36:54.247 --> 36:56.748
- (CRYING)
- MAXINE: <i> Evie?</i>

36:58.685 --> 37:01.278
- OLIVER: Max.
- Oliver, this place is huge.

37:01.280 --> 37:03.388
- I'm still looking.
- Delaine's gonna kill either Nathalie

37:03.390 --> 37:04.655
or Evie. Eric has to choose.

37:04.657 --> 37:05.999
What?

37:07.122 --> 37:09.427
Well, Eric, what's it gonna be?

37:09.429 --> 37:11.729
Mother or daughter?

37:11.731 --> 37:13.264
(CRYING)

37:13.266 --> 37:14.932
I am the one you want.

37:14.934 --> 37:16.134
You just kill me.

37:16.136 --> 37:17.335
It would be my pleasure,

37:17.337 --> 37:19.837
but we established
you're not afraid to die.

37:19.839 --> 37:22.340
In fact, it would be a relief.

37:22.342 --> 37:24.876
So why should I do you the favor?

37:24.878 --> 37:26.850
(EXHALES) Let him kill me.

37:26.852 --> 37:29.080
- Maxine, come on.
- Evie?

37:33.386 --> 37:35.820
Evie. (PANTS)

37:38.425 --> 37:40.224
Evie?

37:41.327 --> 37:43.212
Evie, are you in there?

37:43.214 --> 37:44.620
Evie?

37:45.799 --> 37:47.231
Evie, are you in there?!

37:48.568 --> 37:51.803
♪ ...fun, collecting ♪

37:55.312 --> 37:56.808
DELAINE: <i>Got to move this along, Eric.</i>

37:56.810 --> 37:58.009
No.

37:58.011 --> 37:59.410
It's me you want.

37:59.412 --> 38:00.745
Count of ten.

38:00.747 --> 38:02.280
Don't decide,

38:02.282 --> 38:04.082
I kill 'em both. Ten,

38:04.084 --> 38:06.117
nine,

38:06.119 --> 38:08.820
<i>eight,</i>

38:08.822 --> 38:10.421
- seven,
- I can't let Evie die for me.

38:10.423 --> 38:12.156
- Six,
- You have to let me die.

38:12.158 --> 38:13.925
- Five...
- Please.

38:13.927 --> 38:15.193
Five seconds, Maxine!

38:15.195 --> 38:16.928
<i>- ...four,</i>
- Come on!

38:16.930 --> 38:18.362
Three,

38:18.364 --> 38:19.497
<i>- two,</i>
- (GRUNTS)

38:19.499 --> 38:20.498
and...

38:20.500 --> 38:22.066
(GRUNTS)

38:22.068 --> 38:23.601
<i>...one.</i>

38:23.603 --> 38:24.702
Evie! (GASPS)

38:24.704 --> 38:26.370
<i>- Time's up.</i>
- Max.

38:26.372 --> 38:28.072
<i>- I need a decision.</i>
- Oliver, I've got her.

38:28.074 --> 38:29.941
Eric, Max has got her.

38:29.943 --> 38:31.876
She's got Evie. Wife or daughter, Eric?

38:31.878 --> 38:33.544
Who's gonna live? Nathalie.

38:33.546 --> 38:35.680
- I choose Nathalie.
- Eric, no!

38:35.682 --> 38:37.315
DELAINE: Pretty wife
over pretty daughter.

38:37.317 --> 38:38.583
Surprising.

38:38.585 --> 38:39.817
(WHISPERING): She's safe.

38:39.819 --> 38:41.050
Maxine's got her.

38:41.052 --> 38:42.426
DELAINE: <i>But then again,</i>

38:42.428 --> 38:45.306
<i>you can always have another daughter.</i>

38:49.496 --> 38:50.761
(RADIO STATIC)

38:50.763 --> 38:52.463
Max?

38:52.465 --> 38:54.465
- Max?
- (SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE)

38:54.467 --> 38:56.934
(PANTING) We're fine. We're fine.

38:56.936 --> 39:00.004
- Go.
- (PANTING)

39:00.006 --> 39:02.640
(CRYING)

39:02.642 --> 39:06.177
♪ ♪

39:15.655 --> 39:18.322
♪ ♪

39:38.645 --> 39:40.236
Thank you.

39:41.881 --> 39:43.681
Delaine?

39:43.683 --> 39:46.717
He checked in with
his parole officer on schedule.

39:46.719 --> 39:48.252
So that's it?

39:48.254 --> 39:49.487
We just all

39:49.489 --> 39:50.910
walk away like nothing happened?

39:50.912 --> 39:51.958
Well, Delaine lost.

39:51.960 --> 39:54.155
If you consider $100 million losing.

39:54.157 --> 39:56.427
He wanted a lot more than that.

39:56.429 --> 39:57.862
He wanted to destroy Eric.

39:57.864 --> 39:59.430
He won't stop trying.

39:59.432 --> 40:00.565
He'll be watching us.

40:00.567 --> 40:01.599
All of us.

40:01.601 --> 40:03.428
And we'll be watching him.

40:03.430 --> 40:05.335
I don't know how to thank you all.

40:05.337 --> 40:07.096
Yeah, neither of us do.

40:07.607 --> 40:09.006
You just did.

40:09.849 --> 40:11.709
(”YOUTH” BY DAUGHTER PLAYING)

40:18.051 --> 40:20.885
Listen, I'm gonna drop both
of you back at the house,

40:20.887 --> 40:23.279
and then I'll be leaving.

40:23.823 --> 40:25.356
Don't be silly.

40:25.358 --> 40:27.158
At least stay the night.

40:27.160 --> 40:28.361
Evie would like you to.

40:28.363 --> 40:29.961
I can't.

40:29.963 --> 40:31.537
I mean...

40:34.067 --> 40:36.133
I can't be with you anymore.

40:36.135 --> 40:37.468
With either of you.

40:37.470 --> 40:38.469
It's not safe.

40:38.471 --> 40:41.305
But Delaine could still come after us.

40:41.307 --> 40:42.465
He won't.

40:43.276 --> 40:45.443
Not if he thinks
he's driven me away from you.

40:45.445 --> 40:46.719
(SIGHS)

40:49.661 --> 40:50.994
You...

40:51.557 --> 40:53.317
you wanted me to move on.

40:53.319 --> 40:54.285
No.

40:54.287 --> 40:56.320
Not like this. (CRYING)

40:56.322 --> 40:58.147
Hey.

40:59.092 --> 41:01.292
(EXHALES)

41:02.610 --> 41:04.395
I'm a mess.

41:04.397 --> 41:06.397
Yeah.

41:06.399 --> 41:08.299
A beautiful mess.

41:08.301 --> 41:10.368
(SPUTTERS)

41:10.370 --> 41:11.535
Let's go.

41:12.712 --> 41:14.171
♪ To the finish line ♪

41:14.173 --> 41:15.506
I could use a drink.

41:15.508 --> 41:18.276
I'm not drinking, but I'll join you.

41:18.960 --> 41:20.244
Yeah.

41:20.246 --> 41:22.079
Sure. If you're buying.

41:22.546 --> 41:24.465
Then you're staying.

41:25.718 --> 41:27.652
What are we talking about?

41:27.654 --> 41:29.387
I...

41:29.389 --> 41:32.456
I told Zara I was gonna resign
after all this was done.

41:32.458 --> 41:33.958
Are you kidding me?

41:33.960 --> 41:36.627
Listen, you even think about quitting,

41:36.629 --> 41:39.130
you and I are gonna have
some serious problems.

41:39.132 --> 41:40.398
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

41:40.400 --> 41:41.666
I didn't know you cared.

41:41.668 --> 41:43.534
Now you do.

41:43.536 --> 41:46.637
♪ ♪

41:48.107 --> 41:50.775
One thing is still bothering me though.

41:50.777 --> 41:53.978
That a man like Delaine
could lose and walk away?

41:53.980 --> 41:56.647
He told you he couldn't
violate his parole.

41:56.649 --> 41:59.583
Eric said Delaine's a game player.

42:00.386 --> 42:02.461
What if the game isn't over?

42:04.724 --> 42:07.358
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

42:08.428 --> 42:11.095
♪ ♪

42:14.334 --> 42:18.035
♪ And you caused it ♪

